Business Brief -- Divi Hotels N.V.:
   Reorganization Takes Effect
   As Firm Leaves Chapter 11
On July 25, Divi Hotels filed a reorganization plan
pre-negotiated with its secured lenders, senior and junior
bondholders and preferred shareholders. Under the plan,
virtually all assets of Divi Hotels N.V. were transferred to
a new Delaware corporation, Divi Hotels Inc.
   The company said Divi Hotels N.V. shareholders received
about 1.4% of Divi Hotels Inc.'s common stock on a fully
diluted basis, while bondholders and creditors received the
remaining 98.6% of the new company's shares.